The input array `edges` is not null.
The length of `edges` is equal to `n - 1`, where `n` is the number of nodes in the tree.
The input array `amount` is not null.
The length of `amount` is equal to `n`.
The input integer `bob` is a valid node in the tree, i.e., `0 <= bob < n`.
The values in `amount` are even integers in the range `[-10^4, 10^4]`.
